President Barack Obama has announced the designation of a Presidential Delegation to Monrovia, Liberia to attend the inauguration of Her Excellency Ellen Johnson Sirleaf, President of the Republic of Liberia, on January 16, 2012. The Honorable Hillary Rodham Clinton, Secretary of State, will lead the delegation. Other members of the delegation include U.S. Ambassador to Liberia Linda Thomas-Greenfield, Senator Christopher A. Coons, Assistant Secretary of State Johnnie Carson, Ambassador-at-Large for Global Women's Issues Melanne Verveer, Deputy Administrator Donald Steinberg, Deputy Director of the Peace Corps Carrie Hessler-Radelet, Commander of U.S. Africa Command General Carter F. Ham, and Special Assistant to the President Grant T. Harris.